Subject: rPSA-2007-0149-1 bind bind-utils

rPath Security Advisory: 2007-0149-1
Published: 2007-07-27
Products: rPath Linux 1
Rating: Major
Exposure Level Classification:
    Remote System User Deterministic Weakness
Updated Versions:
    bind=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1/9.3.4_P1-0.1-1
    bind-utils=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//1/9.3.4_P1-0.1-1

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2007-2926
    https://issues.rpath.com/browse/RPL-1587

Description:
    Previous versions of the bind package are vulnerable to
    a cache-poisoning attack due to cryptographically weak
    query id generation.

